{
  "stem": "1282.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 18.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And survival was working for contractors that worked for the government.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The contractor got paid, but we were the free labor to the contractor.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we were allowed to go home at night, come back in the morning.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if we didn't, there was a death warrant out for us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was very difficult to communicate with the family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my family was taken away in 1944 in April.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were taken away to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "An interesting story, when my family was gathered up and taken to a larger town from where they were deported-- And--",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Sevlush. ?] It was-- the city was [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Sevlush. ?] It was a brickyard, and that's where my father, mother, and two sisters were taken.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were in ghetto, and then they were deported, all of them, to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the first time that I was aware that they are not at home anymore is when I received a postcard signed by my mother.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Dear son, we have been repatriated by the German government.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We live on a farm.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We are doing farm work now, but we are together, and we are OK.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So don't worry, and so on and so forth, signed in her handwriting.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What the Germans did is-- evidently, for some political reasons, they didn't want to spread the name of Auschwitz, especially to the Jews in Budapest at that time, [? yet. ?] And then they asked the parents or-- my mother, they asked her, do you have any kids?",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she gave the addresses of the kids.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So she addressed a pre-printed postcard which stated that they had been repatriated all the time to confuse and all the time not to let the reality out.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And mother signed that postcard.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
